Research Update: Siemens AG Upgraded To &#39;AA-&#39; On Successful Portfolio Transformation And Conservative Financial Policy; Outlook

Stable

- Net payments received from captive portfolio run off of about €5 billion in fiscal 2024 and more than €3.5 in fiscal 2025.

We estimate that the principal liquidity uses include:

- Short-term debt maturities of about €9.1 billion in fiscal 2024 and about €5.6 billion in fiscal 2025.

- Annual capex of about €2.2 billion-€2.4 billion.

- Working capital outflow of about €1 billion per year.

- Dividend payment of about €4.2 billion in fiscal 2024 and about €4.6 billion in fiscal 2025.